
Overview of noun diversion

The noun diversion has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) diversion, recreation -- (an activity that diverts or amuses or stimulates; "scuba diving is provided as a diversion for tourists"; "for recreation he wrote poetry and solved crossword puzzles"; "drug abuse is often regarded as a form of recreation")
2. (2) diversion, deviation, digression, deflection, deflexion, divagation -- (a turning aside (of your course or attention or concern); "a diversion from the main highway"; "a digression into irrelevant details"; "a deflection from his goal")
3. (1) diversion, diversionary attack -- (an attack calculated to draw enemy defense away from the point of the principal attack)
